commitResults.messageTitle: Update UG sections on buy and sell command for PE dry run.
Refactor buy command to purchase from supplier at displayed index.
Refactor inventory.hasGood to use GoodName instead of Good.
commitResults.messageBody: Currently hasGood extracts the GoodName out of Good to check if the inventory has a good with the same GoodName. This creates additional baggage. If one wanted to check if a particular GoodName was in the inventory, one would have to wrap that GoodName in a dummy Good to call the hasGood method.

commitResults.messageTitle: Enhance buy command to create transaction history entry.
Reverse using GoodName to check existence of good in inventory.
Refactor Sell command and Good constructors.
commitResults.messageBody:
* Sell item by item's displayed index
* Sell command preserves threshold for each good entry
* Refactored Good constructor. Good should serve as a single inventory record that bundles a good's name with it's stored quantity and warning threshold. When any of those parameters are omitted, default values are used.
Currently it's used to bundle information about an instance of good or good transaction. The danger with this is there is the possibility of unknowingly having default values used, and thus overriding persistent memory. Constructors Good.goodWithName() and Good.newGoodEntry() were made to have this issue made explicit.
